## 2026-05-23 — OTP via SMS.ir: phone login + password reset, end-to-end
**Did:**
- **Backend:**
  - `phone` column added to `users` (required, 10-digit Iranian, unique). New `otp_codes` table (mobile, sha256 `code_hash`, purpose ∈ {`login`, `password_reset`}, `expires_at`, `consumed_at`, `attempts`). Migration `0008_phone_and_otp` — verified from fresh DB.
  - New module set in `app/domains/users/`:
    - `phone.py` — accepts `09…`, `+98…`, `0098…`, `98…`, or bare `9…`, normalizes to `9XXXXXXXXX`; raises `InvalidPhoneNumber` otherwise (409).
    - `sms.py` — SMS.ir `POST /v1/send/verify` client over `httpx.AsyncClient`. When `SMSIR_API_KEY` or `SMSIR_TEMPLATE_ID` is unset (dev/CI), it logs the code at WARNING instead of sending — so we never burn real SMS credits in tests, and devs can copy codes from the log.
    - `otp.py` — code generation (cryptographically random 6 digits), sha256 hash on store, 5-minute TTL, 5-attempt cap, 60-second per-phone resend cooldown. Single uniform `OtpInvalid` error so callers can't distinguish "wrong code" from "expired" from "no pending OTP" via response shape (anti-enumeration).
  - New auth flows on `app/domains/users/service.py`: `register` now requires phone; `start_phone_login` / `complete_phone_login` (passwordless login); `start_password_reset` / `complete_password_reset` (updates password + revokes all existing refresh tokens for defense in depth).
  - New endpoints: `POST /auth/login/otp/request`, `POST /auth/login/otp/verify`, `POST /auth/password-reset/request`, `POST /auth/password-reset/verify`. Request endpoints always return **202** regardless of whether the phone is registered (enumeration protection); only verify endpoints surface OTP errors.
  - New exceptions: `PhoneAlreadyRegistered`, `InvalidPhoneNumber`, `OtpInvalid`, `OtpResendTooSoon`. All map to existing handlers (409, 409, 401, 409 respectively).
  - Added `httpx==0.27.2` to runtime `requirements.txt` (was dev-only).
  - Config additions: `SMSIR_API_KEY` (placeholder), `SMSIR_TEMPLATE_ID` (placeholder), `SMSIR_BASE_URL`, `OTP_CODE_LENGTH`, `OTP_TTL_SECONDS`, `OTP_MAX_ATTEMPTS`, `OTP_RESEND_COOLDOWN_SECONDS`. **API key NOT committed** — placeholder in `.env.example` only.
  - **API key the user pasted in chat should be considered compromised; user must rotate from SMS.ir panel.** Real key goes only in `backend/.env` (gitignored).
  - Tests in `tests/test_users.py`: added phone-normalization test, duplicate-phone test, invalid-phone test, plus 5 new OTP flow tests (full login flow, wrong code, single-use, resend cooldown, full reset flow, reset revokes existing refresh tokens). `tests/conftest.py` admin/user fixtures updated with phone. Used a `fixed_otp` monkeypatch on `app.domains.users.otp.generate_otp_code` so verify-step tests are deterministic. **21/21 user-auth tests pass; full suite 51 pass + 2 still-pre-existing cart failures.**
- **Frontend:**
  - `auth.ts`: `register` now takes `phone`. New helpers `requestLoginOtp`, `verifyLoginOtp`, `requestPasswordReset`, `completePasswordReset` (both verify helpers fetch `/auth/me` after storing the token pair so callers get a `User`).
  - `AuthView`:
    - New `phone` input on signup (required, `dir="ltr"`, numeric input mode).
    - Forgot-password mode is now real — 2-step: (1) enter phone → request OTP → (2) enter code + new password + confirm → verify and auto-login.
    - New `phone-otp` mode: 2-step passwordless login (phone → code → tokens).
    - Mode-switch buttons added: from `login` you can hop into `phone-otp`; from `phone-otp` back to email/password login. The `forgot` link still lives under the login password field.
    - OTP code input is `inputMode="numeric"` with auto-strip of non-digits, large tracking, autoFocused.
    - Status-aware Persian error toasts now also recognize cooldown (409 with "wait" in message) and OTP context (401 → "code wrong/expired").
- **End-to-end smoke test against live uvicorn:**
  - Register `09124301159` → response shows normalized `phone: "9124301159"` ✓
  - `POST /auth/login/otp/request` → 202, code lands in JSON log (`SMS.ir not configured; OTP for mobile=… would be: 433112`) ✓
  - `POST /auth/login/otp/verify` with that code → token pair ✓
  - Replay same code → 401 with uniform `OTP code is invalid or expired` ✓
  - Request OTP for unregistered phone → 202 (no enumeration) ✓
  - `POST /auth/password-reset/request` → 202; verify with wrong code → 401; verify with correct code → token pair; subsequent login with old password → 401; login with new password → success ✓
- `npm run lint` clean, `npm run build` clean, `ruff check . --fix` clean.

**State:** dirty. New backend files: `app/domains/users/{phone,sms,otp}.py`, `alembic/versions/0008_phone_and_otp.py`. Modified: `app/{config,exceptions}.py`, `app/domains/users/{models,crud,schemas,service,router}.py`, `tests/{conftest,test_users}.py`, `requirements.txt`, `.env.example`. Frontend: `src/auth.ts` (additions), `src/App.tsx` (AuthView reshaped). All prior-session uncommitted changes still uncommitted.

**Gotchas / decisions:**
- Phone is **required** at signup per user choice. Migration adds it NOT NULL with no default; safe because no production users exist. For a populated DB, the proper pattern is add-nullable → backfill → set-NOT-NULL.
- "OTP request always 202" means a user who typoed a phone won't see an error — they'll just never get a code. Acceptable trade-off for enumeration protection. Cooldown errors (409) DO surface, so legitimate users hitting their own resend get clear feedback.
- Cooldown only throttles unconsumed OTPs; once verified, the next request immediately returns 202. By design.
- `OtpInvalid` is deliberately one-shot uniform — no different responses for "wrong code" vs "expired" vs "no pending OTP". `OtpResendTooSoon` is the exception (different status, only triggers on the request side).
- The OTP code is sha256-hashed before storage; no plaintext code anywhere. Tests monkeypatch `generate_otp_code` to a fixed value so the verify step is deterministic.

**Action items for the user:**
- **Rotate the SMS.ir API key** that was pasted into the chat earlier (treat as compromised).
- Once your SMS.ir template is approved, paste the templateId and I'll wire it in `.env`.
- `[[project-phone-otp]]` memory updated to reflect that the OTP provider is locked in and the phone column is live.

**Next:**
- Cart UI against `/cart` endpoints (uses `authFetch`). Replace `cartCount: number` with a real cart-items state; rebuild add/remove handlers; fix the two pre-existing `test_orders.py` failures along the way.
- Then orders list + checkout + payment initiate.

